cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.SE

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it proposes a practical anonymity solution for online communications. It may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it implements the solution on a hardware switch and examines its performance. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves designing and implementing a system for anonymity. It could also be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves distributing and routing network traffic. Finally, it may be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it involves programming a hardware switch using the P4 network programming language.
